he Byzantine Empire that controlled his home city of Antioch and the Arabic-speaking cultural universe of Syria-Palestine, Egypt, Aleppo, and Iraq, Ibn al-Fadl engaged intensely with both Greek and Arabic philosophy, science, and literary culture. Challenging the common narrative that treats Christian and Muslim scholars in almost total isolation from each other in the Middle Ages, Alexandre M. Roberts reveals a shared culture of robust intellectual curiosity in the service of tradition that has had a lasting role in Eurasian intellectual history.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mai 2021) 0aChristian philosophyxTranslating into ArabicxHistoryy11th century. 0aChristianity and other religions. 0aPhilosophy, AncientxTranslating into ArabicxHistoryy11th century. 7aHISTORY / Byzantine Empire.2bisacsh  aabdallah ibn al fadl.  aabrahamic religions.  aaleppo.  aancient greece.  aangels.  aantioch.  aantiquity.  aastrology.  aastronomy.  aatoms.  abyzantine.  acosmology.  ademetrius.  adivine inspiration.  aegypt.  agreek texts.  ahistory.  ahoroscope.  ainfinity.  aintellectual history.  airaq.  aisaac the syrian.  aislam.  ajohn of thessaloniki.  akaisarios.  alate antiquity.  aliterary culture.  alogic.  amateriality.  amatter.  anonfiction.  apalestine.  aphilosophy.  aphysics.  areason.  areligion.  arevelation.  ascience.  asophronios.  aspirituality.  astars.  asyria.  atheology.  auniverse.  avoid.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2020 Englishz978311070473008iTitle is part of eBook package: